<DocumentationLayout 
  title="Documentation - RANDSUM"
  description="Complete documentation for the RANDSUM dice rolling library"
>
  <h1>RANDSUM Documentation</h1>
  
  <p class="lead">
    Welcome to the RANDSUM documentation. This comprehensive guide will help you get started with advanced dice rolling for your applications.
  </p>

  <h2>What is RANDSUM?</h2>
  
  <p>
    RANDSUM is a powerful dice rolling library that provides sophisticated notation support for tabletop gaming, probability simulation, and randomization tasks. It's designed for developers who need reliable, feature-rich dice mechanics in their applications.
  </p>

  <h2>Key Features</h2>
  
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Advanced Notation</strong> - Support for complex dice expressions with modifiers</li>
    <li><strong>Game System Support</strong> - Pre-built implementations for popular RPG systems</li>
    <li><strong>TypeScript First</strong> - Full type safety and excellent developer experience</li>
    <li><strong>Extensible</strong> - Easy to extend with custom dice mechanics</li>
    <li><strong>Well Tested</strong> - Comprehensive test suite ensuring reliability</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Getting Started</h2>
  
  <p>
    Ready to start rolling? Check out our <a href="/docs/installation">installation guide</a> to get RANDSUM set up in your project, or jump straight to the <a href="/docs/quick-start">quick start guide</a> to see it in action.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-8">
    <div class="card">
      <h3 class="card-title">Installation</h3>
      <p class="card-description">Get RANDSUM installed and configured in your project</p>
      <a href="/docs/installation" class="btn btn-primary mt-4">Install Now</a>
    </div>
    
    <div class="card">
      <h3 class="card-title">Quick Start</h3>
      <p class="card-description">Learn the basics with simple examples</p>
      <a href="/docs/quick-start" class="btn btn-secondary mt-4">Get Started</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocumentationLayout>
